        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 1 at 5:03PM EDT until August 1 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 503 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 3 miles west of Huntersville to 10 miles southeast of
Gastonia to 4 miles northeast of York, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Gastonia, Uptown Charlotte, Central Charlotte, Southwest Charlotte,
Northwest Charlotte, Mt Holly, Belmont, South Gastonia, Clover, and
Cramerton.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
